This executive summary is provided to comply with 40 CFR ?68.155. 



Facility and Regulated Substances Handled

Location: Air Liquide Electronics US LP, Dallas Chemical Center, 13546 North Central Expressway, Dallas, TX 75243

The maximum intended inventory is 40,000 pounds of 37% Hydrochloric Acid stored in various containers as follows:

-    Heavy Duty HDPE (High Density Polyethylene) bulk totes at 3100 pounds each 

-    1000L totes at 2625 pounds each 

-     55 gallon drums at 506 pounds each

-    One gallon polyethylene bottles at 9.9 pounds each

The bulk liquid aqueous hydrochloric acid is stored in a bulk tote and pumped to stations to fill smaller containers. Bulk liquid totes and smaller trans-filled product containers (bottles or barrels) are stored in the main warehouse area.  Piping is either in double-containment or located within a spill control area and funneled to IWW spill containment via drains/trenches.



General Accidental Release Prevention Program and Chemical-specific Prevention Policies and Steps

This facility complies with EPA's RMP Prevention Program 2 and all applicable state and local codes and regulations.  

Some technological safeties and managerial practices in place that help to prevent or limit releases include:

a) The use of management of change to ensure the covered process is not altered without a safety review;

b) The existence of IW drain secondary containment;

c)  The existence of manual emergency shutdown system;

d)  the establishment of operator training and operating procedures (SOPs); 

e)  the establishment of additional safety training;

f)  the presence of manual isolation valves;

g) the use of a timer on bottle fill to help ensure valves are closed  when bottles are filled;

h) the presence of a scale on MCV fill to help ensure valves close when MCV is filled; and

i) the use of IW drain monitoring for pH by operations personnel for early spill detection.



